Kim Yong Nam Calls for NAM's Increased Role 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Havana, September 16 (KCNA) -- The Non-Aligned Movement (NAM) should put up collective actions against the arbitrary and high-handed practices of a specified country and take more practical measures to establish a new and fair international order.
 Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, said this on Sept. 16 at the 14th NAM summit now under way in Havana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the past 45 years since the declaration of its birth the NAM has served as a banner for the developing countries in their struggle to build an independent and peaceful world based on justice and made a great contribution to the process of transforming the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The desire and aspiration of humankind after the just and peaceful 21st century are still facing serious challenges. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The international order is disturbed and peace and security in the world are seriously threatened by the high-handed acts and unilateralism of the superpower standing in the way of independent choice and development of countries and nations and the non-aligned countries have become their biggest victims. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. has escalated all sorts of despicable moves against the DPRK since Washington singled out it as part of "an axis of evil", a target of preemptive nuclear attack, invariably pursuant to its hostile policy towards Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The grave situation where DPRK's security and interests are exposed to the U.S. threat to mount a nuclear attack on it compelled it to take an option to have access to nuclear weapons as deterrent for self-defence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The government of the DPRK declared more than once that it will feel no need to keep even a single nuke when it is not exposed to the U.S. threat any longer after it has rolled back its hostile policy towards Pyongyang and confidence has been built between the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The nuclear issue between the DPRK and U.S. can be finally resolved only if the U.S. respects the sovereignty and option of the former and makes a switchover from its hostile policy to a policy of peaceful coexistence and basically remove all the nukes and nuclear war threat from the Korean Peninsula and its vicinity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The present international situation requires the NAM to increase its position and role as an independent political force representing the South. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It is our view that the summit should pay a special attention to the following points in setting out the orientation of the NAM's activities to cope with the prevailing situation: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Firstly, the NAM should invariably remain true to its noble idea and principle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Secondly, the NAM should meet all challenges by the force of the unity and solidarity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thirdly, the NAM should put main emphasis on categorically rejecting the double standards in the international relations and ensuring the strict adherence to the principle of equality and impartiality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The government of the DPRK will as ever perform its responsibility and role in the efforts to achieve the human cause of independence and the growth of the NAM.

Kim Yong Nam Meets Algerian President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Havana, September 17 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, in Havana on Sept. 16 met and had a talk with Algerian President Abdelaziz Bouteflika who attended the 14th NAM summit.
 The Algerian President, recollecting that he was received by President Kim Il Sung when he visited Korea on several occasions, said that Kim Il Sung was a veteran statesman of the world as well as the greatest leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Il Sung had unselfishly helped the Algerian people in their struggle for national liberation, he said, adding that Algeria would strive to further develop the friendly and cooperative relations with the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed support for the stand of the DPRK government on national reunification.

DPRK Founding Anniversary Celebrated at Its Missions Abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 18 (KCNA) -- Receptions, photo exhibitions, film shows and friendly gatherings took place at the DPRK missions in Vietnam, Syria, Iran, India, Pakistan, Cambodia, Indonesia, Bangladesh, Nepal, Guinea, Switzerland, the Czech Republic, Britain and Peru and at the DPRK permanent missions in the UN Secretariat and international organizations from Sept. 6 to 9 to celebrate the 58th anniversary of the DPRK.
 Standing before the portraits of President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il were floral baskets and bouquets laid by political parties, governments, ministries, organizations and public figures of relevant countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display at the venues were famous works of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and photos showing the immortal feats of their Songun leadership and introducing the might of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Screened at film shows were Korean films including "The 55th Founding Anniversary of the DPRK." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on invitation were political and public figures and representatives of international and regional organizations and non-governmental organizations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The permanent vice-minister of Foreign Affairs of Vietnam said that the party, government and people of Vietnam support the Korean people in their just cause of achieving peaceful reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The minister of Information and the first vice-minister of Foreign Affairs of Syria pointed out that it is the firm stand of the party and government of Syria to continue to boost the friendly relations with the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The director of the Bureau of External Cooperation of the Ministry of Defense and Armed Forces Logistics of Iran stressed that the Iranian army will always stand with the armed forces of the DPRK in the anti-U.S. struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the New Left Movement of Peru said that it is the result of Kim Jong Il's Songun politics that the banner of socialism is fluttering more powerfully in Korea where the U.S. imperialists' strong-arm policy and arbitrary practice are getting undisguised. The Songun politics is the banner of sure victory in accomplishing the cause of socialism, he stressed.

Symposia on Juche Idea and Songun Policy Held Abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 18 (KCNA) -- Symposia on the Juche idea and Songun politics took place at Callao National University of Peru, the Group for the Study of the Juche Idea of Teachers of the Normal College Faculty of Chambogo University of Uganda and the Kazak Association for Studying and Disseminating the Juche Idea Named after Comrade Kim Jong Il from Sept. 6 to 11 on the occasion of the 58th founding anniversary of the DPRK.
 Roberto Carbonel Pezo, chairman of the Peru-Korea Friendship Institute for Study of the Juche Based Songun Policy, in a speech titled "Role of Songun politics" said that the Songun policy is the outstanding one which helps the Korean people to firmly defend their dignity and build a great prosperous powerful nation of Juche, ever victorious one which enables them to defeat any aggressor at one stroke. The DPRK, not a big country, has emerged a powerful country thanks to the Songun politics, an all-powerful treasured sword, he said, adding: The DPRK is a socialist country centering on the popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chief of the Ugandan group at a symposium on Kim Jong Il's famous work "Socialism of Our Country Is a Socialism of Our Style as the Embodiment of the Juche Idea" said that the DPRK has covered the path of victory because it has the Juche idea founded by President Kim Il Sung and enriched by Kim Jong Il as its guideline. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called for deeply understanding the Juche idea which crystallizes perfect guiding idea, theory and method of the present times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Members of the Kazak association in their speeches titled "Songun politics guarantees peace on the Korean Peninsula" and so on said that the Korean people have smashed the U.S. imperialists' moves to isolate and stifle them and firmly defended the sovereignty of the country and the dignity of the nation with the might of great Songun politics. They called for actively applying the Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message of greetings to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the symposium in Kazakhstan.

Exploits of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il Lauded in Bangladesh 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 18 (KCNA) -- A joint celebration meeting was sponsored by the Left Democratic Front of Bangladesh and the Bangladesh-DPRK Friendship and Solidarity Committee in Dhaka on Sept. 8 on the occasion of the 58th founding anniversary of the DPRK.
 Hassanul Huq Inu, chairman of the Central Executive Committee of the National Socialist Party of Bangladesh, the chairman of the Bangladesh-DPRK Friendship and Solidarity Committee, and other speakers noted that President Kim Il Sung successfully accomplished the cause of the building of the state after leading the great anti-Japanese war to victory and General Secretary Kim Jong Il, while successfully carrying forward the President's revolutionary cause, is wisely leading the Korean people in their struggle to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation by his Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Socialism of the DPRK is a pattern for the world people in building a new society, they said, and stated: It is a highly important matter for the progressives to frustrate the imperialists' moves to stifle the DPRK and defend socialism. The Bangladeshi people will invariably support the Korean people in their struggle to protect the sovereignty of the country and achieve national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A national celebration meeting, an art performance and a film show took place under the sponsorship of the Peruvian-Korean Institute of Culture and Friendship in Lima on Sept. 7. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The celebration meeting was addressed by Yuri Cesar Castro Romero, secretary general of the institute, Genaro Ledesma Izquieta, chairman of the People's Front of Workers, Peasants and Students of Peru, and other figures, who in unison highly praised the exploits of the President in the building of the state and said the DPRK would always throw its rays to the world as Kim Il Sung's and Kim Jong Il's Korea as it has the great Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il and powerful military force and the might of single-minded unity to firmly defend its sovereignty and dignity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting was followed by an art performance by Peruvian artistes and shows of the Korean films "The great leader Comrade Kim Jong Il gives on-the-spot guidance to different fields" and "New appearance of Korea."

Scientists Help Promote Modernization of National Economy
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 18 (KCNA) -- The February 17 Shock Brigade of Scientists and Technicians, formed with scientists, teachers and researchers in Juche 67 (1978), takes a big share in promoting the modernization of the national economy in the DPRK.
 They, dispatched to hundreds of units of the socialist economic construction of the country, have applied thousands of research achievements and technical innovations to practice in collaboration with producer masses, thus making a healthy profit for the state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The members of the shock brigade active at the Pyongyang Rubber Factory are playing the pivotal role in renewing the production processes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They made devices of automatically measuring various kinds of compound materials and laid the foundation for remote-controlling all the production processes of synthetic rubber. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Ryongbuk Foodstuff Factory is manufacturing various kinds of bean food, enjoying popularity with the people. It owes the success to the efforts of the shock brigade. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The factory has developed and introduced a method of extracting oil from beans without heat, remarkably improved the quality of synthetic meat and succeeded in establishing the process of making bean-curd with cooling soybean cake. It is now building the flexible bean-curd production process. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Similar successes have been reported from textile mills in Pyongyang, Sinuiju, Sariwon and other parts of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The shock brigade members working at the textile mills are striving hard with a goal to change the looms of all the mills in the country with flexible rapier weaving looms and renovate all the production facilities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those at the Pyongyang Textile Machine Plant have already finished the three-dimensional design for flexible rapier weaving loom and built a one-ton class low-frequency induction furnace, extending the serviceable life of the furnace four to five times and raising productivity 1.5 times as compared with the old one.
